    <item>
      <name>Qwer-uiop-to-aset-niop</name>
      <appendix>This does exactly what it says, it makes the top row of letters into the asetniop keyboard.</appendix>
      <appendix>This also changes the t,y, f,g,h and j keys into some missing interpunction signs for easy</appendix>
      <appendix>reaching.</appendix>
      <identifier>remap.asetniop.qweruiop</identifier>
      <block>
        <autogen>__KeyToKey__ KeyCode::Q, KeyCode::A</autogen>
        <autogen>__KeyToKey__ KeyCode::W, KeyCode::S</autogen>
        <autogen>__KeyToKey__ KeyCode::R, KeyCode::T</autogen>
        <autogen>__KeyToKey__ KeyCode::U, KeyCode::N</autogen>
        <autogen>__KeyToKey__ KeyCode::T, KeyCode::SLASH</autogen>
        <autogen>__KeyToKey__ KeyCode::Y, KeyCode::BACKSLASH</autogen>
        <autogen>__KeyToKey__ KeyCode::F, KeyCode::BRACKET_LEFT</autogen>
        <autogen>__KeyToKey__ KeyCode::J, KeyCode::BRACKET_RIGHT</autogen>
        <autogen>__KeyToKey__ KeyCode::G, KeyCode::MINUS</autogen>
        <autogen>__KeyToKey__ KeyCode::H, KeyCode::EQUAL</autogen>
      </block>
    </item>
    <item>
      <name>Cmd to Shift</name>
      <appendix>This changes around a few of the functional keys on the left side of your keyboard.</appendix>
      <appendix>* Change left cmd key to sticky shift key.</appendix>
      <appendix>* Change fn key to option key.</appendix>
      <appendix>* Change left option key to cmd key.</appendix>
      <appendix>It also makes the space bar &amp; left cmd key into an enter key when pressed simultaneously.</appendix>
      <identifier>remap.asetniop.cmd-to-shift</identifier>
      <autogen>__KeyToKey__ KeyCode::COMMAND_L, KeyCode::VK_STICKY_SHIFT_L</autogen>
      <autogen>__KeyToKey__ KeyCode::FN, KeyCode::OPTION_L</autogen>
      <autogen>__KeyToKey__ KeyCode::OPTION_L, KeyCode::COMMAND_L</autogen>
      <autogen>__SimultaneousKeyPresses__ KeyCode::COMMAND_L, KeyCode::SPACE, KeyCode::RETURN</autogen>
    </item>
    <item>
      <name>Cmd to C</name>
      <appendix>This is here purely for practicing with the asetniop web version.</appendix>
      <appendix>* Change left cmd key to "C" key.</appendix>
      <appendix>* Change fn key to option key.</appendix>
      <appendix>* Change left option key to cmd key.</appendix>
      <appendix>It also makes the space bar &amp; "C" key into an enter key when pressed simultaneously.</appendix>
      <identifier>remap.asetniop.cmd-to-c</identifier>
      <autogen>__KeyToKey__ KeyCode::COMMAND_L, KeyCode::C</autogen>
      <autogen>__KeyToKey__ KeyCode::FN, KeyCode::OPTION_L</autogen>
      <autogen>__KeyToKey__ KeyCode::OPTION_L, KeyCode::COMMAND_L</autogen>
      <autogen>__SimultaneousKeyPresses__ KeyCode::C, KeyCode::SPACE, KeyCode::ENTER</autogen>
    </item>
  </item>
</root>
